侧重位置与方向的改变。
普通用词，指从一处到另一外的任何距离的转移。

与touch可换用，但语气强一些，运用范围广些。

bilingual.target: 她会随着它的阴影移动。

bilingual.source: You can move the heels up and down.
So we just move round the table.
bilingual.target: 所以我们只是绕着桌子移动。

bilingual.source: These boats can break ice as they move.
bilingual.target: 这些船在移动时可以破冰。

bilingual.source: A very old man tried to move the mountains.
bilingual.target: 一个非常老的男人试图移动大山。

bilingual.source: If you move a bit, we'll all be able to see.
bilingual.target: 如果你稍微移动一下，我们都能看到。

bilingual.source: He can move the jaw and eyebrows to create the look he wants.
bilingual.target: 他可以移动下巴和眉毛来创建他想要的表情。

bilingual.source: When Jon moves the skeleton, the skin and clothes move with it.
bilingual.target: 当乔恩移动骨架时，皮肤和衣服也会跟着动。

bilingual.source: Because the character has a skeleton, it can move like a real person.
bilingual.target: 因为角色有骨架，它可以像真人一样移动。

list.abstract: move的基本意思是“动”,可指人体姿势的改变，更多的是指人〔物〕位置的移动，引申还可表示“（使）动摇，（使）醒悟”“（使）感动”等，强调某种起促动作用的动因，外界影响或内在动机。作此解时，可用作不及物动词,也可用作及物动词，作及物动词时接名词、代词作宾语，也可接以动词不定式充当补足语的复合宾语,意为“促使（某人）做某事”。
《MOVE》是由서지음作词，Curtis A Richardson、Adien Lewis、Angelique Cinelu作曲，泰民演唱的一首歌曲，发行于2017年10月16日。

yingyinNormal.en: Microbots can move anything, anywhere, with ease.
yingyinNormal.zh: 微型机器人，可以轻松移动任何物体至任何地方。

yingyinNormal.en: Jill would have seen him move slightly further down the track, resulting in her seeing the ball follow a triangular path.
yingyinNormal.zh: 吉尔会看到杰克和火车一起向前移动，结果她看到的球是以三角形的路线移动的。

yingyinNormal.en: Once you've got these on here, don't move them for at least 10 minutes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一旦你到了这一步，放置10分钟不要移动。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't just move up and down. Don't just look up. Look backwards, sideways, around corners.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不要只上下移动，不要只往上看，还要往回看，往旁边看，看转角周围。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: And because speed is distance divided by time, Jill actually sees the ball move faster.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为速度等于距离除以时间，事实上 吉尔所看到球比杰克所看到的移动得更快。

yingyinNormal.en: It also predicts that when objects move, they generate a pulse that propagates through space-time, a bit like waves through water.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它还预测，当物体移动时，它们会产生脉冲，通过时空传播，有点像波浪过水。

yingyinNormal.en: But if they meet up again later to compare watches, less time would have elapsed on Jack's watch, balancing the fact that Jill saw the light move further.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是如果他们在实验结束后相遇比对彼此手表时，他们会发现杰克的手表会走慢一些，因此解释了这事实：吉尔看到的光移动得更远。

yingyinNormal.en: If you move the car, you will break the web. But how am I going to get to work? Don't worry, Daddy. You can borrow my little bicycle. Here you are. Thank you, Peppa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你移动了车子，网就被破坏了。但是我要怎么去上班呢？别担心爸爸，你可以借我的小自行车来用啊。爸爸，给你。谢谢你，佩奇。

yingyinNormal.en: Ooh! Bad move. Really? Why?
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，这一步没走好。真的? 为什么?

yingyinNormal.en: Don't move. I'll go get one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别动，我去给你拿。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. Let's move on. All right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，我们继续。好吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Dad, why did we move to a motel?
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸，为什么我们要搬到汽车旅馆去?

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon will move out eventually.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿终究会搬出去的。

yingyinNormal.en: Lucas? Don't move, just calm down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 卢卡斯？别乱动，冷静下来。

yingyinNormal.en: Because I had to. I had to move on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我别无选择，我必须向前看。

yingyinNormal.en: This is as fast as I move! Calm down!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我最快只能走这么快！冷静！

yingyinNormal.en: Tell me what you know or move along. No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要么告诉我你知道什么要么滚蛋。不。

yingyinNormal.en: She could have forgotten to log the move.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她可能忘了把挪动记录下来了。

yingyinNormal.en: The Wuxi finger hold? That's my best move.
yingyinNormal.zh: 无须铁指扣？这是我的绝招。

yingyinNormal.en: Mike, if you hadn't move our schedule up...
yingyinNormal.zh: 麦克，要不是你加快行程…

word_family.mean: v. 动；移动；改变位置；改变状态；进展；发展；在…中进行社交活动；动议；提议；使（肠）排空

sense_info_list.en: make progress; develop in a particular manner or direction
sense_info_list.zh: 发展; 进步; 前进

examination_example.sentence: We know we are <highlight>moving</highlight> into a period where the jobs in demand will change rapidly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要知道，我们正在进入这样一个时期，需求中的工作将会迅速发生变化。

examination_example.sentence: When you start conversation from there and then <highlight>move</highlight> outwards, you'll find all of a sudden that the conversation becomes a lot easier.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当你从共同点开启对话，然后向外拓展，你会突然发现对话变得容易多了。

examination_example.sentence: Furthermore, these losses make us mature and eventually <highlight>move</highlight> us toward future opportunities for growth and happiness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 更重要的是，这些失去让我们成熟，最终让我们走向未来的成长和幸福的机会。

sense_info_list.en: take action; suggest something, especially formally at a meeting or in a law court

examination_example.sentence: In Britain the <highlight>move</highlight> towards open access publishing has been driven by funding bodies.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在英国，开放出版是由资助机构推动的。

examination_example.sentence: Here are five simple ways that you can make the first <highlight>move</highlight> and start a conversation with strangers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这里有五个简单的方法，你可以迈出第一步，开始与陌生人交谈。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>move</highlight> turned out to be foresighted.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实证明，此举是有先见之明的。

sense_info_list.en: change or cause to change from one state, opinion, sphere, or activity to another

examination_example.sentence: A <highlight>move</highlight> back to self-sufficiency, the argument goes, would boost the farming industry, political sovereignty and even the nation's health.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种观点认为，回归自给自足将促进农业发展、政治主权甚至国家健康。

examination_example.sentence: For someone <highlight>moving</highlight> from finance to advertising, maybe they want to look more "SoHo."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对于那些从金融业转到广告业的人来说，也许他们想看起来更“SoHo”。

examination_example.sentence: Beethoven's music tends to <highlight>move</highlight> from chaos to order as if order were an imperative of human existence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 贝多芬的音乐往往从混乱变得有序，好像秩序对人类的存在是极为重要的。

sense_info_list.en: (cause to) change position
sense_info_list.zh: 改变位置; 移动; 动作

examination_example.sentence: It <highlight>moved</highlight> around alone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它独自移动。

examination_example.sentence: Meanwhile, the asocial robot simply <highlight>moved</highlight> forwards and backwards and side to side.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，非社交型机器人只是简单地前后左右移动。

examination_example.sentence: The robot rats were quite minimalist, resembling a chunkier version of a computer mouse with wheels-to <highlight>move</highlight> around and colorful markings.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些机器老鼠非常简约，就像一个胖乎乎的带有轮子的电脑鼠标，可以四处移动，还带有彩色的标记。

sense_info_list.en: an act of changing the place where you live or work

examination_example.sentence: Some western farmers have responded by <highlight>moving</highlight> operations to Mexico.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 西部的农民已经将生产转移到墨西哥。

examination_example.sentence: The Navy Department <highlight>moved</highlight> into the east wing in 1879.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 海军部门在1879年搬到了东翼。

examination_example.sentence: Newlyweds traditionally <highlight>move</highlight> in with the wife's parents and may live with them up to a year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 按照传统，新婚夫妇要搬去和女方的父母同住，可能会和他们一起住长达一年的时间。

sense_info_list.en: propose for discussion and resolution at a meeting or legislative assembly

examination_example.sentence: Legislation is <highlight>moving</highlight> through the House that would save USPS an estimated $28.6 billion over five years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 众议院正在通过一项法案，该法案将在五年内为美国邮政节省约286亿美元。

examination_example.sentence: Macy's has been <highlight>moving</highlight> aggressively to try to remake itself for a new era of shopping.

examination_example.sentence: Morgan said those findings were part of the decision not to <highlight>move</highlight> forward with Governor Bill Haslam's proposal.

examination_example.sentence: It will slash staffing at its fleet of 770 stores, a <highlight>move</highlight> affecting some 3, 000 employees.

word_usage.usage:
move是及物动词，表示“感动”应该用be moved。
示例：她感动落泪。
She was moved to tears.

move是瞬间动词，不可与表示一段时间的状语连用。
示例：我一年前搬到了北京。
误 I have moved to Beijing for a year.
正 It is a year since I moved to Beijing.
短语move house“搬家”是固定短语，在house前不能加饰任何修饰语和限定语。

examination_example.sentence: His parents would <highlight>move</highlight> into his new house.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的父母将搬进他的新房子。

examination_example.sentence: The daughter feared her mother would be ignored there, and so she decided to <highlight>move</highlight> her into a more welcoming facility.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 女儿担心母亲在那里会被忽视，所以她决定让她搬到一个更受欢迎的机构。

sense_info_list.en: (cause to) change position
sense_info_list.zh: 改变位置; 快速移动

examination_example.sentence: For example, with the help of robots, people can clean their houses without even <highlight>moving</highlight> their butts.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，在机器人的帮助下，人们甚至不用挪动屁股就可以打扫房子。

examination_example.sentence: San Jose was among the best cities in America for poor kids to <highlight>move</highlight> up the social ladder.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 圣何塞是美国贫困儿童提升社会地位的最佳城市之一。

examination_example.sentence: For instance, you can <highlight>move</highlight> a TV to the kitchen and watch your favorite shows while you're standing at the sink.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，你可以把电视移到厨房，站在水槽边看你最喜欢的节目。

sense_info_list.en: make progress; develop in a particular manner or direction

examination_example.sentence: Developed and developing countries are <highlight>moving</highlight> in opposite directions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 发达国家和发展中国家正朝着相反的方向发展。

examination_example.sentence: That vision is <highlight>moving</highlight> closer to reality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这一愿景正越来越接近现实。

examination_example.sentence: New technologies will, and should, be developed. This is how society <highlight>moves</highlight> forward. However, progress can't be one-sided.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新技术将会并且应该被开发出来。这就是社会前进的方式。但是，进步不能是单方面的。

sense_info_list.en: take action; suggest something; especially formally at a meeting or in a law court
sense_info_list.zh: 提议; 采取行动; 行动; 计划

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>move</highlight> is due to global warming and rising sea levels.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这一举动是由于全球变暖和海平面上升。

examination_example.sentence: Such <highlight>moves</highlight> may eliminate the fears of those living in the exporting countries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些举措可能会消除那些生活在出口国的人的恐惧。

examination_example.sentence: The more children <highlight>moved</highlight>, the better their grades were in school, particularly in the basic subjects of math, English and reading.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子运动越多，他们在学校的成绩就越好，尤其是在数学、英语和阅读等基础学科。

sense_info_list.en: cause someone to have strong feelings; such as sadness; sympathy; happiness; or admiration

examination_example.sentence: You might as well call it the Year of the Lunch Box, thanks in large part to a genius <highlight>move</highlight> by a Nashville-based manufacturer, Aladdin Industries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你不妨将其称为午餐盒年，这在很大程度上要归功于总部位于纳什维尔的制造商阿拉丁工业公司的天才之举。

sense_info_list.en: to change; to change something
sense_info_list.zh: (使)改变状态(或观点、领域、活动)

examination_example.sentence: And social media use has <highlight>moved</highlight> from a periodic activity to a daily one in the same period.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在同一时期，社交媒体的使用已经从周期性活动转变为日常活动。

sense_info_list.en: influence or prompt someone to do something

sample.mean: v. 去掉；除去；废除；取消；远离；隔代的；隔亲的；除掉；转移；调动

word_usage.usage:
move是及物动词，表示“感动”应该用be moved。
示例：她感动落泪。
She was moved to tears.

move是瞬间动词，不可与表示一段时间的状语连用。
示例：我一年前搬到了北京。
误 I have moved to Beijing for a year.
正 It is a year since I moved to Beijing.
短语move house“搬家”是固定短语，在house前不能加饰任何修饰语和限定语。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指激起勇气和信心，侧重鼓励，有时含"启发灵感"之意。
move 与 touch 可换用，但语气强一些，运用范围广些。
指某人或某物运动的过程或方式。
着重朝某一方向的移动，通常用单数。
通常抽象地指有规则的动作或定向运动，特指政治性的运动。

word_family.mean: v. 动；移动；改变位置；改变状态；进展；发展；在…中进行社交活动；动议；提议；使（肠）排空

examination_example.sentence: I had to admit that <highlight>moving</highlight> so often made me feel lonely.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我不得不承认，经常搬家让我感到孤独。

examination_example.sentence: As I was growing up, we were often on the <highlight>move</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在我成长的过程中，我们经常搬家。

examination_example.sentence: He'd <highlight>moved</highlight> to England with his mum when he was three and it had been 13 years since I'd last seen him.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他三岁的时候和妈妈一起搬到了英国，距离我上次见到他已经13年了。

sense_info_list.zh: 移动; 行动; 迁移

examination_example.sentence: Before I knew it an hour had passed and it was time to <highlight>move</highlight> on to lunch.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不知不觉一个小时过去了，该去吃午饭了。

examination_example.sentence: Larry told her that he had already put out the fire and she should not <highlight>move</highlight> in case she injured her neck.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Larry告诉她，他已经把火扑灭了，她不应该动，以防伤到脖子。

examination_example.sentence: The tasters <highlight>move</highlight> down the line with surprising speed, tasting from a spoon and deciding what is a fair price for each tea.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 品茶师以惊人的速度依次品尝，用勺子品茶，然后决定每一杯茶的合理价格。

examination_example.sentence: Our roles in the factory were simple: Place cakes on a <highlight>moving</highlight> belt.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们在工厂里的角色很简单：把蛋糕放在传送带上。

examination_example.sentence: That way, cattlemen will know whether they need to <highlight>move</highlight> their cattle to another field for nutrition purposes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这样，养牛人将知道他们是否需要将他们的牛转移到另一片田地以获得营养。

examination_example.sentence: Lamb and mother reunited, I turned back to the tractor only to see it <highlight>move</highlight> suddenly away from me.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 小羊和妈妈团聚了，我转身走向拖拉机，却看到它突然离开了我。

sense_info_list.en: (cause to) change position
sense_info_list.zh: 改变位置; 移动; 动作

examination_example.sentence: On Earth, the air is always <highlight>moving</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在地球上，空气总是在运动中。

examination_example.sentence: While skipping rope, you have to <highlight>move</highlight> rapidly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 跳绳时，你必须快速移动。

examination_example.sentence: His perfect <highlight>moves</highlight> make it even harder to believe that this kid learned these skills in less than two years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他完美的动作让人们更难相信这个孩子在不到两年的时间里学会了这些技能。

sense_info_list.en: change one's place of residence or work

examination_example.sentence: The two factories were <highlight>moved</highlight> outside the city last year．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这两家工厂去年搬到了城外。

examination_example.sentence: Paul has found a new job and is considering <highlight>moving</highlight> to a new flat near his company.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 保罗找到了一份新工作，正在考虑搬到公司附近的新公寓。

examination_example.sentence: After he took courses in useful life skills, he recently <highlight>moved</highlight> into his own flat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在学习了有用的生活技能课程后，他最近搬进了自己的公寓。

sense_info_list.en: make progress; develop in a particular manner or direction
sense_info_list.zh: 发展; 进步; 前进

examination_example.sentence: Writing about bad feelings can also help brains get over them and <highlight>move</highlight> on.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 写下不好的情绪也可以帮助大脑克服它们，然后继续前进。

examination_example.sentence: As we <highlight>move</highlight> into the future, 3D printing will revolutionize the way we shop and the way we treat sick people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着我们走向未来，3D打印将彻底改变我们的购物方式和治疗病人的方式。

examination_example.sentence: Some writers may rewrite a single paragraph many times before <highlight>moving</highlight> on.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些作者可能会多次重写一个段落之后才会继续下一段。

sense_info_list.en: cause someone to have strong feelings, such as sadness, sympathy, happiness, or admiration

examination_example.sentence: Hi, Mom <highlight>moved</highlight> me to tears.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 嗨，妈妈让我感动得流下了眼泪。

examination_example.sentence: The father was <highlight>moved</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 父亲感动了。

examination_example.sentence: His story <highlight>moves</highlight> us a lot.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的故事使我们深受感动。
